<p class="title">Chapter 5: The Obstinate One (No.05)</p>
<p class="para">Hee hee! Are we gossiping
here? I hope you don't mind if
I join in, because Mama has a
juicy little morsel to share.</p>
<p class="para">So when I went to check on
that adventurer the other day,
I found him moaning and
groaning as he hung from a
cliff by one hand. His arm is
as thick as my entire body,
and yet there it was, just
slip, slip, slipping away!</p>
<p class="para">Well, I was so shocked,
I yelped in surprise! And I
<i>knew</i> his record didn't end
there, so it was all quite
embarrassing, let me tell you.
</p>
<p class="para">...Hmm? What happened next?
<br>Well, just as he was about to
fall, I heard his wife yell.
<br>She was cradling their little
girl and staring at him with
THAT look, so I knew he was in
real trouble. Then she demanded
that he stop training and come
play with his daughter!</p>
<p class="para">
Can you believe it? The man
was just <i>training</i>! And right
after she yelled at him, he
switched hands and started
humming to himself! I swear,
some people...</p>
